text: Itkuchukovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Abitovsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 235 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Meleuz, 7 km from Basurmanovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Meleuzovsky District
title: Itkuchukovo
